 A businessman and a farmer were reportedly killed in separate incidences by suspected herdsmen in Ondo State. According to reports, the men were killed in Molege community, Ose council area and Ondo town in Ondo West council area of the state. It was gathered that at Molege, a farmer, Zacheus Olotu, from Oka Akoko, Akoko South West council area, was abducted. He was later found dead in the bush. Olotu and his wife were reportedly on their way to farm when they were abducted between Ifon and Molege by some herdsmen. The wife was released hours later to source for ransom. It was gathered that a search carried out by security operatives after they were alerted led to the discovery of Zacheus’s body in the forest. His corpse had been deposited at Iwaro Oka General Hospital, a police source said. The Olubaka of Oka, Oba Yusufu Adebori Adeleye, insisted that the security agencies in the state should get to the root of the matter and arrest the culprits. In a related development in Ondo town, a 45-year-old businessman, Sunday Okeke, otherwise called Sunny White, was reportedly shot dead on his way to Anambra State. The victim, sources said, was travelling in company with two of his friends when they were attacked. A police source said that the abductors shot the man while he attempted to run into a nearby bush as others were being whisked away. Chioma, wife of the deceased, who expressed shocked at the news of her husband’s death, urged the security agencies to fish out his killers. 